Description:
NOTE:
SP2 & Later - With the new Design Studio V2 project, all the individual customization elements (like, action wizard, domain wizard, smartform wizard, workflow designer etc) are clubbed together into the same product (Design Studio V2) to simplify customization.
 
Hence the creating and editing of SmartForm's etc will be from Design Studio V2 itself (as supposed to be from Expert Share folder) earlier.
------------------------
 
Estimated Duration: 10 minutes
 
In Visual Studio, create a new custom controller (if you make changes to the generated controller, these will be overwritten and lost when the controller is re-generated each time the SF is saved)
1. Add a class to a project that will overwrite the base controller scripts for any custom scripting required
              a. In Solution Explorer, right-click on the .smartform file and select "Add custom smartform logic"
2. Add custom scripting to overwrite the default behaviour
              a. Open the generated controller file AND the custom controller file
              b. In the GENERATED controller file, copy the namespace at the top of the file, then in the CUSTOM controller, replace the existing namespace with the one copied from the generated file
              c. In the GENERATED controller file, copy the public partial class name from the top of the script to the custom controller
                  e.g. Generated controller had
                           public partial class BaseSmartFormController : BaseSmartFormControllerBase {
                               private static readonly ILogWriter logWriter = Logger.Current.GetLogWriter();
                  Into the Custom controller, enter:
                            public partial class BaseSmartFormController
              d. In the custom controller, create partial class methods to overwrite the base logic in the generated controller. Example below is what would replace what was previously stored in SFW scripting points which would then have been generated into an IronPython controller: 
 
Form level:                 OnLoaded = self.LogWriter.Log(LogLevel.Error, 'OnLoaded script for Advanced SmartForm')
                                  OnValidate = self.LogWriter.Log(LogLevel.Error, 'OnValidate script for Advanced SmartForm')
                                  OnDataChanged=self.LogWriter.Log(LogLevel.Error, 'OnDataChanged script for Advanced SmartForm')
 
Control level:              OnChange=self.LogWriter.Log(LogLevel.Error, 'Client has changed')
 
---------------------Example of content from custom controller below to replace scripting points above ---------------------------
 
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using System.Text;
using Aderant.Framework;
using Aderant.Framework.Logging;
 
namespace Aderant.SmartForms.SmokeTest
{
    public partial class BaseSmartFormController
    {
        protected override void OnInitialized()
        {
            base.OnInitialized();
            //KM Added log for Base SmokeTest. Previously entered in OnLoaded scripting point in SFW for IronPython controller 
            logWriter.Log(LogLevel.Error, "OnLoaded script for Advanced SmartForm");
        }
        public override void Validate()
        {
            base.Validate();
            //KM Added log for Base SmokeTest. Previously entered in OnValidate scripting point in SFW for IronPython controller 
            logWriter.Log(LogLevel.Error, "OnValidate script for Advanced SmartForm");
        }
        protected override void OnDataChanged(string dataName)
        {
            base.OnDataChanged(dataName);
            //KM Added log for Base SmokeTest. Previously entered in OnDataChanged scripting point in SFW for IronPython controller 
            logWriter.Log(LogLevel.Error, "OnDataChanged script for Advanced SmartForm");
        }
        protected override void OnClientChanged()
        {
            base.OnClientChanged();
            //KM Added log for Base SmokeTest. Previously entered in OnDataChanged scripting point in SFW for IronPython controller 
            logWriter.Log(LogLevel.Error, "Client has changed" );
 
        }
    }
}

E.g. After updating data in one control, default data into another
 
In SFW,
(a) Add control that you wish to default data from
(b) Add control that you wish to default data to
 
 
In VS,
(a) For your SmartForm, add custom controller to your SmartForm project (refer to...)
 
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using System.Text;
 
namespace Aderant.SmartForms.SFControls {
    public partial class TextBoxController {
 
        }
    }
}
 
(b) Add override class for the data control that you are defaulting FROM e.g. 
 
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using System.Text;
 
namespace Aderant.SmartForms.SFControls {
    public partial class TextBoxController {
        protected override void OnForDataChangeChanged() {
            base.OnForDataChangeChanged();
        }
 
    }
}
 
 
(c) Within the override method, add script to default/set the data
 
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using System.Text;
 
namespace Aderant.SmartForms.SFControls {
    public partial class TextBoxController {
        protected override void OnForDataChangeChanged() {
            base.OnForDataChangeChanged();
            DefaultFromData = ForDataChange;
        }
 
    }
}

